{"author":{"id":"1949ffc23f11a8cb4f8c42a45c9ad241b49570df9a18687489e9ea78d87c54a3"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1772206473,"nonce":"wUDn1UqJXYSW0KOIeW+cX9f3xns=","title":"Favicon: create simplified logo variant for small display","message":"The studio header now uses feedbax studio v5.svg as the logo. For the favicon, a simplified variant is needed that reads clearly at 16–32px.\n\n**This requires user action — do not attempt to generate the SVG programmatically.**\n\nAsk the user to:\n1. Open feedbax studio v5.svg in Affinity Designer\n2. Create a variant with: tighter horizontal viewBox (remove excess left/right padding), no arrow element, and joints (circle + square) sized to remain visible at 16px\n3. Export with \"Flatten transforms\" checked\n4. Save as `feedbax favicon.svg` at the repo root\n\nOnce the file exists, integrate it as the favicon in `web/public/` (replacing or supplementing the existing icon.svg).","files":null}]}